oss’ Muses Almanach in 1796 and later became known under the title Who will buy Gods of Love?, to trace the modern transformations undergone in the pictorial arts, literature and music by the late antique motif of love gods. The study moves from Stabiae and Pompeii via Goethe and Thorvaldsen through to Pushkin and ends with reflections on the turn of the millennium.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aGerman poetryxHistory and criticismx19th century. 0aGerman poetryy19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 4aLiebesgott. 4aMotiv. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aLove God.  aMotif.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE UND GESCHICHTE 2008z9783110209426oZDB-23-DGE0 cprintz978311020291540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311021010140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110210101423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110210101/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGEb2008  aZDB-23-DGGb2008  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014